    "actions_taken": [
      "First aid administered by platform medic",
      "Medivac called and injured person flown to hospital",
      "Recommended pulling tool acquired after incident"
    ],
    "summary": "On 25 June 2021 at 1045 hours, a deck operator at MC 807 B (Olympus) received lacerations and contusions to the right hand while removing liner tubes from produced water hydrocyclones. The operator was using a come-a-long pulling tool (non-recommended equipment) when the liner suddenly popped free and struck the operator's hand. The operator was under medical care from 25 June to 5 July 2021 and returned to full duty work on 6 July 2021.",
